From 9de0134496f69bc802c60665eea80227609ec02c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: libiao <1102510224@qq.com>
Date: Sat, 28 Mar 2026 09:48:50 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] adjust threadpool concurrency using scheduler statistics

Sample process CPU usage and context-switch rates in the thread pool timer
thread and use them to adapt a global active worker quota.

Add Tp_statistics in threadpool_unix.cc to track normalized CPU usage,
voluntary context-switch frequency (ru_nvcsw), involuntary context-switch
frequency (ru_nivcsw), and the derived active_threads_quota used by the
scheduler. Expose the current scheduler inputs through
Threadpool_statistics_detail, and also export the current global active and
waiting thread counts through SHOW STATUS.

Use these statistics to control concurrency growth by shrinking
active_threads_quota when CPU usage or context-switch pressure is high and
growing it again when pressure drops. Apply the quota in the queue dequeue,
worker wakeup, and wait paths, and maintain a global active-thread counter
so quota checks reflect the current runnable worker population.

Add THD_WAIT_ORDER_COMMIT_FLUSH and instrument ordered commit flush/sync
waits with thd_wait_begin()/thd_wait_end(). When
thread_pool_enable_extra_threads is enabled, the thread pool can wake or
create a worker on order-commit flush waits if the group still has queued
work and available quota.

Add the following global sysvars and basic sys_vars coverage:
- thread_pool_commit_burst_threads
- thread_pool_cpu_usage_threshold
- thread_pool_nvcsw_freq_threshold
- thread_pool_nivcsw_freq_threshold
